{"actual_usd":0.157475,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":280,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30655,"reply":"\"Well, if he's only an example, then the cross becomes a very dramatic illustration lesson.\" *I rub my thumb along the edge of my Bible and glance out across the square, where the morning light is catching on the water between the houses.* \"And that doesn't account for the way Scripture talks about sin, guilt, forgiveness, and rescue. An example can show me what love looks like. An example cannot carry my sin, reconcile me to God, or do for me what I cannot do for myself.\"\n\n\"The heart of it is this: Jesus did not come only to say, 'Live like this.' He came to do something.\" *I lift one shoulder a little.* \"If all I need is instruction, then maybe a sermon on a hillside would be enough. But if I'm actually lost—if sin is not just bad technique but rebellion, bondage, death—then I need more than a teacher. I need a Savior. That's why the cross matters. 'While we were yet sinners, Christ died for us.'\"\n\n*I look back at you, gentler now.* \"A good man living well can inspire me. The Son of God dying and rising can save me. That's a very different thing. Was there some particular version of the 'Jesus as moral example' idea that got under your skin, or are you just pulling at the foundation a little?\"","rolling_24h_usd":51.86211000000003,"run_id":"791db320-37a2-4110-beba-c40454e8e4d6"}
